[0.007, "o", "\u001b[1;3Hhttps://php.net/ignore-user-abort\u001b[2;2Hignore_user_abort = On\r\n\u001b[27X\u001b[4;3HDetermines the size of the realpath cache to be used by PHP. This value should\r\n; be increased on systems where PHP opens many files to reflect the quantity of\u001b[6;3Hthe file operations performed.\u001b[7;3HNote: if open_basedir is set, the cache is disabled\u001b[8;3Hhttps://php.net/realpath-cache-size\u001b[9;2Hrealpath_cache_size = 4096k\u001b[11;3HDuration of time, in seconds for which to cache realpath information for a given\u001b[12;3Hfile or directory. For systems with rarely changing files, consider increasing this\u001b[13;3Hvalue.\u001b[18X\u001b[14;3Hhttps://php.net/realpath-cache-ttl\r\n;realpath_cache_ttl = 120\r\n\u001b[17X\u001b[17;3HEnables or disables the circular reference collector.\u001b[18;3Hhttps://php.net/zend.enable-gc\r\nzend.enable_gc =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[9X\u001b[21;3HIf enabled, scripts may be written in encodings that are incompatible with\u001b[22;3Hthe scanner.  CP936, Big5, CP949 and Shift_JIS are the examples of such\u001b[23;3Hencodings.  To use this feature, mbstring \u001b[30m\u001b[103mexten\u001b[m\u000fsion must be enabled.\u001b[24;2Hzend.multibyte = Off   \u001b[26;3HAllows to set the default encoding for the scripts.  This value will be used\u001b[27;3Hunless \"declare(encoding=...)\" directive appears at the top of the script.\u001b[28;3HOnly affects if zend.multibyte is set.\u001b[29;2Hzend.script_encoding = \u001b[31;3HAllows to include or exclude arguments from stack traces generated for exceptions.\u001b[32;3HIn production, it is recommended to turn this setting on to prohibit the output\u001b[33;3Hof sensitive information in stack traces\u001b[34;3HDefault Value: Off   \r\n; Development Value: Off\u001b[36;2H Production Value: On\r\nzend.exception_ignore_args =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[20X\u001b[39;3HAllows setting the maximum string length in an argument of a stringified stack trace\u001b[40;2H to a value between 0 and 1000000.\r\n; This has no effect when zend.exception_ignore_args is enabled.\u001b[42;3HDefault Value: 15\u001b[40X\u001b[43;2H Development Value: 15\r\n; Production Value: 0\u001b[45;3HIn production, it is recommended to set this to 0 to reduce the output\u001b[26X\u001b[46;2H of sensitive information in stack traces.\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f360,45         18\u001b[48;7H\u001b[?25h"]
